The role
Reporting to the GM / Head of Commercial Finance,  the role plays a key part in linking finance and operations. 

A well-established and growing national group is seeking a capable and commercially minded finance expert to join their Queensland sites. This role suits someone with a strong manufacturing / commercial base who is now looking to broaden their impact to work closely with operations, supply chain and senior leadership to improve performance and decision-making.
This role will combine month-end responsibilities with project work, reporting, and business partnering across inventory, procurement, and sales functions. The scope is broad and offers visibility across the business - key responsibilities will include:

Prepare monthly management reports and variance analysis
Support budgeting, forecasting, and financial planning processes
Partner with manufacturing and commercial teams to deliver insights that improve operational efficiency and revenue growth.
Work collaboratively with the accounting and FP&A teams to deliver timely, accurate and insightful financial reports and analysis.
Lead cost analysis across production inputs and identify margin improvement opportunities.
Support pricing strategies, product profitability analysis, and customer deal evaluations.
Partner with key managers on business performance
Support system improvements, data integrity, and reporting efficiency
As the successful candidate, you will possess:

CA/CPA qualification with proven experience in a commercial or management accounting role
Ideally background in product-based environments 
Strong Excel and financial systems experience (SAP preferred)
Good communication skills and an interest in operational drivers of performance
A practical, hands-on approach and willingness to engage across different business units
This is a well-rounded role in a grounded and collaborative team, offering the chance to influence commercial outcomes and develop in a stable, well-regarded business.
Our client is looking at running interviews as soon as possible, so please apply directly, but if you have any queries, please call David McLaren on 0492 458 557.

We are seeking a Senior Business Analyst to support a range of projects within a broader program of work within the ICT Division of a government agency. In this role you will report to the relevant Director and Project Manager and will independently apply business analysis skills to a range of projects. As part of this role you will:

Work with stakeholders to identify and analyse the current state and desired future state of business systems and processes.
Gather and document requirements using departmental templates
Take a user-centered design approach to the development of Business Analyst artefacts.
Key duties and responsibilities

Analyse and model business processes and identify opportunities for improvement. Develop comprehensive business process models, roadmaps, and implementation plans, ensuring that proposed improvements are well-understood and communicated with stakeholders.
Collaborate with data analysts and data scientists to leverage data and analytics for process improvement and informed decision-making.
Gather and document requirements: Elicit and record the needs of stakeholders, translating them into clear specifications for development teams.
Compile and present data, reports, and recommendations to stakeholders and executives.
Create data models, process diagrams, and wireframes to visualize potential solutions, using industry standard techniques.
Act as a liaison between business stakeholders and technical teams, ensuring clear communication and understanding.
Collaborating with subject matter experts, end users, product owners, change managers, architects, developers, database administrators, testers and trainers to design and deliver solutions.
Essential skills & experience

Exceptional ability to confidently elicit and define epics, user stories & acceptance criteria following best practice principles as well as identifying and defining non-functional requirements (NFR).
Exceptional communication skills and ability to facilitate interviews, workshops and engage with a wide variety of stakeholders to successfully document business processes and requirements. Apply and monitor appropriate use of modelling and analysis tools, methods and standards.
Ability and experience in the application of user centred design principles and tools including personas, service blueprints and journey maps to ensure technology investments meet user requirements and align with business goals and strategic objectives.
Experience applying Business Analysis practice to Business Problems supporting solution development in an emerging technology area.
7+ years’ experience in a similar role.
A demonstrable passion for innovation and a dedication to working collaboratively building strong relationships with stakeholders, taking into account individual views and ideas and tailoring the approach.
Strong organisational and time management skills are needed to handle multiple projects and meet deadlines.
Please note that you must be an Australian citizen with a current security clearance to be considered.
  
These roles are based on site in Canberra. Hybrid / remote / work from home options are not available. 
  
NEXT STEPS
  
If you think this could be the right opportunity for you APPLY TODAY or for further information, please contact lindsey@pinpointtalent.com.au or Zac@pinpointtalent.com.au

About our Client
  
Our client is a specialist construction and field services organisation, delivering protective coating, asset maintenance and remediation services across large, asset-heavy environments.
  
The business operates across multiple core systems and is investing heavily in its data capability to move from fragmented reporting to a centralised, scalable analytics platform. As part of this journey is building a central Azure based data lake to support enterprise-wide reporting and core data insight.
  
About the Role   
  
This is a senior, hands-on Data Analyst role, working closely with a highly experienced Senior Data professional. 
  
The focus of the role is on data integration, ingestion and transformation, sitting between source systems and the Power BI reporting layer. This role is critical in designing and building the ETL pipelines and data flows that enable reliable, trusted reporting and overall strong architecture. 
  
The environment has limited documentation, so this role suits someone who is comfortable working hands-on, navigating ambiguity, and building strong data foundations from the ground up.
  
Key Responsibilities   

Build and maintain ETL / ELT pipelines from multiple operational systems into a central data lake.
Design and manage data integration and ingestion processes, including API-based integrations.
Develop clean, reliable and scalable datasets to support Power BI reporting.
Work closely with a Senior Data architect to align data flow, modelling and best-practice design.
Support and improve reporting from ERP and field service platforms (e.g. Jobpac / construction ERP systems).
Operate effectively in a low-documentation environment, taking ownership of data discovery and structure.
Key Requirements   

Proven experience in a Data Analyst or similar role within complex, operational environments.
Strong hands-on experience with ETL processes and data integration and Advanced SQL skills.
Solid experience with Power BI, including data modelling and semantic layer design.
Experience working with APIs and system integrations.
Strong understanding of data flow, data best practice and analytics enablement.
Ability to work closely with senior technical stakeholders and operate autonomously.
